alternative_order.description:
alternative_order mime-type[/mime-subtype] [ mime-type[/mime-subtype] ... ]
unalternative_order { * | mime-type[/mime-subtype] ... }
**alternative_order** command permits you to define an order of preference that is used by NeoMutt to determine which part of a **multipart/alternative** body to display. A *mime-subtype* of "**\***" matches any **multipart/alternative** subtype, as does an empty *mime-subtype*.**unalternative_order** removes entries from the ordered list or deletes the entire list when "**\***" is used as an argument.

