lists.description:
lists [ -group name ... ] regex [ regex ... ]
unlists [ -group name ... ] { * | regex ... }
subscribe [ -group name ... ] regex [ regex ... ]
unsubscribe [ -group name ... ] { * | regex ... }
NeoMutt maintains two lists of mailing list address regular expressions, a list of subscribed mailing lists, and a list of known mailing lists. All subscribed mailing lists are known.The **lists** command adds a mailing list address to the list of known mailing lists. The **unlists** command removes a mailing list from the lists of known and subscribed mailing lists.The **subscribe** command adds a mailing list to the lists of known and subscribed mailing lists. The **unsubscribe** command removes it from the list of subscribed mailing lists.The **-group** flag adds all of the subsequent regular expressions to the *name*d group.

