score.description:
score pattern value
unscore { * | pattern ... }
The **score** command adds *value* to a message\'s score if *pattern* matches it. *pattern* is a string in the format described in the *PATTERNS* section below. *value* is a positive or negative integer. A message\'s final score is the sum total of all matching score entries.The **unscore** command removes score entries from the list. You must specify the same *pattern* specified in the **score** command for it to be removed. The pattern "**\***" is a special token which means to clear the list of all score entries.

