spam.description:
spam regex format
nospam { * | regex }
NeoMutt has generalized support for external spam-scoring filters. By defining your spam *regex*s with the **spam** and **nospam** commands, you can limit, search, and sort your mail based on its spam attributes, as determined by the external filter. You also can display the spam attributes in your index display using the %H selector in the \$index_format variable. (Tip: try \"%\<H?\[%H\] \>\" to display spam tags only when they are defined for a given message).For further information on spam-scoring filters, please consult the section "**Spam Detection**" in the NeoMutt manual.

